Recorded in Public Records 7/14/2021 10:28 AM OR Book 8574 Page 297,
Instrument #2021077286, Pam Childers Clerk of the Circuit Court Escambia
County, FL Recording $27.00
EXHIBIT 2
Escambia County Community Redevelopment Agency
Residential Roof Funding Program
Administered By: Escambia County Neighborhood and Human Services Department
Community Redevelopment Agency
Lien Agreement
Applicant Name
Judy Walker-Kyle
an unmarried woman
Lester L. Walker
an unmarried man
Address of Property
702 E. Johnson
Pensacola, Florida 32514
Total Amount of Lien
Property Reference No.
12-1S-30-7000-035-009
$14,200
I, the undersigned owner of the residential property referenced above, more
particularly described in the Quit Claim Deed recorded in Official Record Book 5596 at
page 1542 of the public records of Escambia County, Florida, agree that the improved
residential property will continue to be used as my primary residence for a period of not
less than five (5) years from the date this lien agreement is recorded in the public records.
The amount secured by this lien shall be due and payable in total for a period of five
(5) years from the date this Lien Agreement is recorded in the public records. Upon
documentation of compliance with the provisions of this Lien Agreement and the Escambia
County Residential Roof Funding Program, and five (5) years subsequent to the
recording of the Lien Agreement in the public records, this lien shall depreciate to zero (0).
I understand that this lien will not be subordinated under any circumstances.
If the property is sold or if ownership or possession or any interest in the Property
is otherwise conveyed, or if the funding agreement executed concurrently with this Lien
Agreement is terminated prior to the expiration of five (5) years, I agree that I or my
successors or assigns will repay the total amount of the residential roof funds secured by
this lien.
